WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.420 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.420 --> 00:00:12.900 align:middle line:84%
Hello, my delicious
co-creators.

00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:13.720 align:middle line:90%
Lilou here.

00:00:13.720 --> 00:00:16.840 align:middle line:84%
I'm in Glasgow today
in Scotland with David.

00:00:16.840 --> 00:00:17.700 align:middle line:90%
Hello David.

00:00:17.700 --> 00:00:19.391 align:middle line:84%
Hello, Lilou, and
how are you today?

00:00:19.391 --> 00:00:21.450 align:middle line:10%
Very good.
I love your accent.

00:00:21.450 --> 00:00:22.780 align:middle line:84%
Yes, Scottish
through and through.

00:00:22.780 --> 00:00:24.190 align:middle line:90%
I grew up in this area.

00:00:24.190 --> 00:00:25.760 align:middle line:90%
I studied in Glasgow.

00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:28.570 align:middle line:84%
I went to university
here, my degree and PhD,

00:00:28.570 --> 00:00:30.740 align:middle line:84%
both about-- in fact
about three minutes

00:00:30.740 --> 00:00:32.401 align:middle line:84%
walk from where we're
sitting right now.

00:00:32.401 --> 00:00:33.100 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:00:33.100 --> 00:00:38.390 align:middle line:84%
And this is kind of a dream
come true for you, unexpected,

00:00:38.390 --> 00:00:40.670 align:middle line:84%
your life went in an
unexpected way, not

00:00:40.670 --> 00:00:45.710 align:middle line:84%
really the way that you who had
studied, but this is quite big.

00:00:45.710 --> 00:00:47.720 align:middle line:84%
Tomorrow you are speaking
in the big auditorium

00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:49.920 align:middle line:84%
here on the river?
-Yeah.

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:53.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm speaking at the Scottish
Exhibition Conference Center.

00:00:53.260 --> 00:00:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And it's the biggest self-help
conference ever in Scotland.

00:00:56.820 --> 00:00:59.930 align:middle line:84%
And it's all Hay House authors,
So it's Hay House, I can do it.

00:00:59.930 --> 00:01:00.790 align:middle line:90%
And I'm so excited.

00:01:00.790 --> 00:01:05.870 align:middle line:84%
Because I visualized
this about 10 years ago.

00:01:05.870 --> 00:01:09.860 align:middle line:84%
12 years ago actually, I did
my very first public event.

00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:12.190 align:middle line:84%
I had resigned from-- I
used to be a scientist

00:01:12.190 --> 00:01:13.400 align:middle line:90%
in the pharmaceutical industry.

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:17.230 align:middle line:84%
I had resigned and did my
very, very first event.

00:01:17.230 --> 00:01:20.280 align:middle line:84%
And there was only
13 people at it.

00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:22.070 align:middle line:90%
I was all filled with big ideas.

00:01:22.070 --> 00:01:23.420 align:middle line:90%
I thought, I'm leaving my job.

00:01:23.420 --> 00:01:25.070 align:middle line:84%
I'm speaking for lots
and lots of people.

00:01:25.070 --> 00:01:26.020 align:middle line:90%
And there's was 13.

00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:28.350 align:middle line:84%
Nine of them were
family and friends.

00:01:28.350 --> 00:01:30.491 align:middle line:84%
And three of them came because
I met them in a cafe the week

00:01:30.491 --> 00:01:31.190 align:middle line:90%
before.

00:01:31.190 --> 00:01:33.901 align:middle line:84%
And they only came if
they didn't have to pay.

00:01:33.901 --> 00:01:35.160 align:middle line:84%
So only one--
-It was free.

00:01:35.160 --> 00:01:36.690 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:01:36.690 --> 00:01:39.420 align:middle line:84%
So only one person
really paid, really came.

00:01:39.420 --> 00:01:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And afterwards, I
thought, I'm not

00:01:41.320 --> 00:01:44.590 align:middle line:84%
very good at this organizing
pf the event situation

00:01:44.590 --> 00:01:46.340 align:middle line:84%
because it's cost
me a lot of money.

00:01:46.340 --> 00:01:48.190 align:middle line:84%
And I was feeling
a bit dejected.

00:01:48.190 --> 00:01:50.600 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, the
workshop went really well.

00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:52.602 align:middle line:84%
And in that moment, I
was saying, damn it,

00:01:52.602 --> 00:01:53.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to make this work.

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:56.650 align:middle line:84%
I immediately visualized
myself speaking

00:01:56.650 --> 00:01:59.790 align:middle line:84%
alongside Wayne Dyer and
Louise Hay and a few others.

00:01:59.790 --> 00:02:02.350 align:middle line:84%
And I decided it was going
to be at the Scottish

00:02:02.350 --> 00:02:04.310 align:middle line:84%
Exhibition Conference
or the Clyde Auditorium

00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:05.215 align:middle line:90%
as it's known as.

00:02:05.215 --> 00:02:05.915 align:middle line:90%
And I decided.

00:02:05.915 --> 00:02:07.046 align:middle line:90%
I didn't set a time on it.

00:02:07.046 --> 00:02:08.479 align:middle line:84%
I just said, that's
what I was going to do.

00:02:08.479 --> 00:02:10.449 align:middle line:84%
And this image
popped into my mind

00:02:10.449 --> 00:02:14.830 align:middle line:84%
at the time of Wayne Dyer
speaking and finishing

00:02:14.830 --> 00:02:17.540 align:middle line:84%
and I came on right after Wayne
and I got a big high five.

00:02:17.540 --> 00:02:20.090 align:middle line:84%
And it's funny because tomorrow,
I'm right after Wayne Dyer.

00:02:20.090 --> 00:02:23.010 align:middle line:84%
So I'll see if the
high five happens.

00:02:23.010 --> 00:02:25.180 align:middle line:84%
At least I visualized
it 12 years ago.

00:02:25.180 --> 00:02:29.040 align:middle line:84%
It's a big achievement
to have-- well,

00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:32.360 align:middle line:84%
to me the most amazing
thing about your whole story

00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:38.050 align:middle line:84%
is that you were working for
the pharmaceutical industry.

00:02:38.050 --> 00:02:39.540 align:middle line:90%
You were well paid.

00:02:39.540 --> 00:02:41.790 align:middle line:84%
You had everything.
It's all set.

00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:46.710 align:middle line:84%
But one day you decided to
resign because it no longer fit

00:02:46.710 --> 00:02:48.310 align:middle line:90%
with your perception of things.

00:02:48.310 --> 00:02:52.440 align:middle line:84%
No, yeah, I did
my PhD in a field

00:02:52.440 --> 00:02:55.520 align:middle line:84%
called organic chemistry, which
basically you build molecules.

00:02:55.520 --> 00:02:56.660 align:middle line:90%
You stick atoms together.

00:02:56.660 --> 00:02:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And in the pharmaceutical
industry where I ended up

00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:02.640 align:middle line:84%
after my PhD, I was building
and developing drugs

00:03:02.640 --> 00:03:04.630 align:middle line:90%
for heart disease and cancer.

00:03:04.630 --> 00:03:07.990 align:middle line:84%
But I started to notice,
when we tested the drugs,

00:03:07.990 --> 00:03:10.425 align:middle line:84%
you give 100 people a drug
and 100 people the fake drug,

00:03:10.425 --> 00:03:12.460 align:middle line:84%
a placebo, which
is made of sugar,

00:03:12.460 --> 00:03:14.520 align:middle line:84%
blackboard chalk,
these type of things.

00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:15.640 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing in it really.

00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:18.610 align:middle line:84%
But incredibly, loads and
loads of people get better.

00:03:18.610 --> 00:03:22.160 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes almost as many
on the placebo as people

00:03:22.160 --> 00:03:22.870 align:middle line:90%
actually on the drug.

00:03:22.870 --> 00:03:25.850 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, wow, what
on earth is going on here?

00:03:25.850 --> 00:03:29.990 align:middle line:84%
So in my spare time I started
to research what happens

00:03:29.990 --> 00:03:31.640 align:middle line:90%
when you have a thought?

00:03:31.640 --> 00:03:34.120 align:middle line:84%
I think we grow up,
certainly in the West,

00:03:34.120 --> 00:03:35.784 align:middle line:84%
we grow up with this idea
that you have a thought

00:03:35.784 --> 00:03:36.550 align:middle line:90%
and it just disappears.

00:03:36.550 --> 00:03:40.040 align:middle line:84%
It's a floaty thing that
has no power whatsoever.

00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:41.690 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, no
that's not correct.

00:03:41.690 --> 00:03:43.820 align:middle line:84%
Because when you have a
thought, you start to change

00:03:43.820 --> 00:03:45.240 align:middle line:90%
the chemistry of your brain.

00:03:45.240 --> 00:03:47.100 align:middle line:84%
And if you think the same
thought over and over again,

00:03:47.100 --> 00:03:49.550 align:middle line:84%
you begin to shape the
actual physical structure

00:03:49.550 --> 00:03:50.530 align:middle line:90%
of the brain.

00:03:50.530 --> 00:03:53.040 align:middle line:84%
And the placebo effect
works in the sense

00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:55.720 align:middle line:84%
that when you believe something
or expect a drug to work,

00:03:55.720 --> 00:03:58.240 align:middle line:84%
even if it's a placebo,
you change brain chemistry

00:03:58.240 --> 00:04:02.190 align:middle line:84%
and you also impact on some
of the physiological processes

00:04:02.190 --> 00:04:03.300 align:middle line:90%
inside the body.

00:04:03.300 --> 00:04:04.720 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
this is incredible.

00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:07.095 align:middle line:90%
People must know about this.

00:04:07.095 --> 00:04:09.280 align:middle line:84%
So even though I was
in a well paid job,

00:04:09.280 --> 00:04:10.610 align:middle line:84%
I completely lost
interest in making

00:04:10.610 --> 00:04:12.810 align:middle line:90%
drugs, no interest at all.

00:04:12.810 --> 00:04:14.877 align:middle line:84%
Because I couldn't-- it
was so interesting for me,

00:04:14.877 --> 00:04:15.610 align:middle line:90%
the power of the mind.

00:04:15.610 --> 00:04:16.950 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't let it go.

00:04:16.950 --> 00:04:18.220 align:middle line:90%
So I just decided to resign.

00:04:18.220 --> 00:04:20.740 align:middle line:90%


00:04:20.740 --> 00:04:24.560 align:middle line:84%
I resigned to start writing
books and giving public talks.

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:25.850 align:middle line:84%
You self-published
your first book.

00:04:25.850 --> 00:04:27.390 align:middle line:90%
I did.

00:04:27.390 --> 00:04:29.100 align:middle line:90%
I didn't mean to self-publish.

00:04:29.100 --> 00:04:31.760 align:middle line:84%
I contacted every main
publisher in the UK

00:04:31.760 --> 00:04:33.890 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't really
go for it at the time.

00:04:33.890 --> 00:04:35.740 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
well, I'm determined

00:04:35.740 --> 00:04:37.720 align:middle line:84%
to write a book so I'm
just going to do it anyway.

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:39.950 align:middle line:90%
And this was back in 2005.

00:04:39.950 --> 00:04:41.420 align:middle line:90%
So I just self-published.

00:04:41.420 --> 00:04:44.210 align:middle line:84%
But then Hay House picked it
up really quickly after that.

00:04:44.210 --> 00:04:48.480 align:middle line:84%
And my other six books are
with Hey House as well.

00:04:48.480 --> 00:04:51.820 align:middle line:84%
And your latest one came
out in October, 2012.

00:04:51.820 --> 00:04:52.520 align:middle line:90%
Yep.

00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:54.670 align:middle line:84%
It's called "Is Your
Life Mapped Out?"

00:04:54.670 --> 00:04:56.890 align:middle line:84%
And the subtitle is
"Unraveling the Mystery

00:04:56.890 --> 00:04:59.120 align:middle line:90%
of Destiny versus Free Will."

00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:00.810 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to
also speak about that.

00:05:00.810 --> 00:05:03.300 align:middle line:84%
But first I would love
to see how you started.

00:05:03.300 --> 00:05:06.050 align:middle line:90%
So you quit that job.

00:05:06.050 --> 00:05:09.260 align:middle line:84%
You starting writing this book
and what kind of evidence--

00:05:09.260 --> 00:05:12.100 align:middle line:84%
because you really bridge
science with spirituality.

00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:15.550 align:middle line:84%
How did you-- what
had happened there?

00:05:15.550 --> 00:05:17.740 align:middle line:84%
What kind of research
have you done and papers

00:05:17.740 --> 00:05:20.490 align:middle line:84%
you put together
or facts that are

00:05:20.490 --> 00:05:23.930 align:middle line:84%
really mind boggling that
you can present to us today?

00:05:23.930 --> 00:05:25.620 align:middle line:84%
Well, the first thing
I started researching

00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:29.680 align:middle line:84%
was placebo effect and studying
what happens in the brain

00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:30.910 align:middle line:90%
chemically.

00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:34.180 align:middle line:84%
And how does a placebo
effect occur inside the body?

00:05:34.180 --> 00:05:37.020 align:middle line:84%
And that naturally led me
into all the different ways

00:05:37.020 --> 00:05:38.070 align:middle line:90%
that mind impacted the body.

00:05:38.070 --> 00:05:40.760 align:middle line:84%
So I ended up
researching meditation.

00:05:40.760 --> 00:05:43.110 align:middle line:84%
And I don't publish
any of my own research

00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:45.210 align:middle line:84%
because there's
so much out there.

00:05:45.210 --> 00:05:47.476 align:middle line:84%
So I find myself taking
the complex stuff

00:05:47.476 --> 00:05:50.010 align:middle line:84%
that's out there that most
people don't understand.

00:05:50.010 --> 00:05:52.950 align:middle line:84%
Because you take a scientific
paper, publication,

00:05:52.950 --> 00:05:54.690 align:middle line:90%
it's full of jargon.

00:05:54.690 --> 00:05:57.560 align:middle line:84%
Even just looking at the
abstract, the summary,

00:05:57.560 --> 00:05:59.040 align:middle line:90%
it's still full of jargon.

00:05:59.040 --> 00:06:01.380 align:middle line:84%
So I started to take--
most of my books

00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:03.390 align:middle line:90%
have 200 to 300 references.

00:06:03.390 --> 00:06:05.830 align:middle line:84%
And I compile all that
and compact it down.

00:06:05.830 --> 00:06:08.060 align:middle line:84%
And my thing, if
you care to call it,

00:06:08.060 --> 00:06:11.090 align:middle line:90%
my thing is explaining stuff.

00:06:11.090 --> 00:06:13.900 align:middle line:84%
So what I do is I take the
complex stuff and I package it

00:06:13.900 --> 00:06:16.931 align:middle line:84%
in a simple way that my mom
and dad and my Auntie Jean

00:06:16.931 --> 00:06:18.670 align:middle line:84%
can read.
-And my kid.

00:06:18.670 --> 00:06:21.160 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, and kids can read
and understand and think,

00:06:21.160 --> 00:06:22.850 align:middle line:90%
yeah, that's really easy.

00:06:22.850 --> 00:06:25.510 align:middle line:84%
So when I first
started doing this,

00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:28.010 align:middle line:84%
it was placebo effect,
then meditation.

00:06:28.010 --> 00:06:31.550 align:middle line:84%
And there was so much stuff
on how meditation can impact

00:06:31.550 --> 00:06:33.980 align:middle line:84%
the heart and how meditation
could structurally

00:06:33.980 --> 00:06:34.950 align:middle line:90%
impact to the brain.

00:06:34.950 --> 00:06:39.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you listen to the
sound of your breathing

00:06:39.240 --> 00:06:40.880 align:middle line:84%
and you impact
several brain regions.

00:06:40.880 --> 00:06:42.520 align:middle line:84%
And if you practice
over and over again,

00:06:42.520 --> 00:06:44.790 align:middle line:84%
you actually shape the
physical structure of the brain

00:06:44.790 --> 00:06:47.080 align:middle line:84%
and the top of the brain
here, the prefrontal cortex.

00:06:47.080 --> 00:06:50.490 align:middle line:84%
You actually physically
shape the structure.

00:06:50.490 --> 00:06:51.570 align:middle line:90%
Neuroplasticity?

00:06:51.570 --> 00:06:52.600 align:middle line:90%
Neuroplasticity, yeah, yeah.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:55.380 align:middle line:84%
And even visualizing
itself, not just meditating

00:06:55.380 --> 00:06:58.770 align:middle line:84%
on the sound of your breath, but
visualizing something happening

00:06:58.770 --> 00:07:01.040 align:middle line:84%
in your life, you
also physically shape

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:02.150 align:middle line:90%
the structure of the brain.

00:07:02.150 --> 00:07:04.290 align:middle line:84%
And through neuroplasticity,
the brain can even be

00:07:04.290 --> 00:07:06.610 align:middle line:90%
thought of as akin to a muscle.

00:07:06.610 --> 00:07:09.650 align:middle line:84%
If you exercise a muscle, it
gets stronger and develops.

00:07:09.650 --> 00:07:13.050 align:middle line:84%
So if you visualize something
or imagine the same thing

00:07:13.050 --> 00:07:15.010 align:middle line:84%
over and over again,
the brain also

00:07:15.010 --> 00:07:16.790 align:middle line:90%
begins to change like a muscle.

00:07:16.790 --> 00:07:19.500 align:middle line:84%
And in many ways, some
of the things I realized

00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:21.790 align:middle line:84%
is the brain can't distinguish
between whether something's

00:07:21.790 --> 00:07:24.730 align:middle line:84%
actually happening or whether
you're just imagining it.

00:07:24.730 --> 00:07:25.440 align:middle line:90%
And that's great.

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:28.100 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're imagining
healing or changing your life,

00:07:28.100 --> 00:07:30.920 align:middle line:84%
then in many ways, once
you've done it's a memory.

00:07:30.920 --> 00:07:32.610 align:middle line:84%
It's already happened
for your brain.

00:07:32.610 --> 00:07:35.040 align:middle line:84%
And the skill then is
to get out of the way.

00:07:35.040 --> 00:07:37.640 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by
getting out of the way,

00:07:37.640 --> 00:07:42.750 align:middle line:84%
stop believing that
you can't for example.

00:07:42.750 --> 00:07:44.350 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that's a big one.

00:07:44.350 --> 00:07:45.770 align:middle line:90%
That's a big, big one.

00:07:45.770 --> 00:07:47.770 align:middle line:84%
I really enjoyed
this conversation,

00:07:47.770 --> 00:07:51.340 align:middle line:84%
because it shows us that
really anything is possible.

00:07:51.340 --> 00:07:55.500 align:middle line:84%
And then we wonder why this
information is not out anymore.

00:07:55.500 --> 00:07:58.770 align:middle line:84%
Were you stopped at
any time of the way

00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:00.850 align:middle line:84%
by other pharmaceutical
business?

00:08:00.850 --> 00:08:03.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean how did they react
so when you stopped?

00:08:03.410 --> 00:08:08.900 align:middle line:84%
Well for me, I found it
relatively easy because what

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:11.310 align:middle line:84%
I do is I back up
everything I say

00:08:11.310 --> 00:08:15.030 align:middle line:84%
and everything I write
about with solid science.

00:08:15.030 --> 00:08:17.390 align:middle line:84%
And I don't really try
to make any enemies.

00:08:17.390 --> 00:08:20.330 align:middle line:84%
I'm not out there telling
people, you can use your mind.

00:08:20.330 --> 00:08:22.710 align:middle line:84%
If a person's got cancer,
I'm not saying use your mind

00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:24.250 align:middle line:90%
and forget medical advice.

00:08:24.250 --> 00:08:26.150 align:middle line:90%
I say do both.

00:08:26.150 --> 00:08:28.620 align:middle line:84%
Take medical advice but
use your mind as well.

00:08:28.620 --> 00:08:31.070 align:middle line:90%
Not instead of, but as well as.

00:08:31.070 --> 00:08:33.640 align:middle line:84%
In the past, we wouldn't
use the mind at all.

00:08:33.640 --> 00:08:36.740 align:middle line:84%
So by going through
this mechanism,

00:08:36.740 --> 00:08:41.010 align:middle line:84%
I guess, and I'm asking people
to live their life in the way

00:08:41.010 --> 00:08:42.559 align:middle line:90%
they would normally live it.

00:08:42.559 --> 00:08:44.300 align:middle line:84%
Take the advice they
can ordinarily take,

00:08:44.300 --> 00:08:47.740 align:middle line:84%
but here is the power of
the mind as well as that,

00:08:47.740 --> 00:08:50.350 align:middle line:84%
and then we start to develop
this feeling inside ourselves,

00:08:50.350 --> 00:08:52.500 align:middle line:84%
this faith in
ourselves that we have

00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:54.190 align:middle line:90%
far more than we think we are.

00:08:54.190 --> 00:08:55.790 align:middle line:84%
And who knows where that
will actually lead to

00:08:55.790 --> 00:08:57.120 align:middle line:90%
in terms of our capabilities.

00:08:57.120 --> 00:09:00.000 align:middle line:84%
