00:12:41.290 --> 00:12:44.300 align:middle line:84%
What I often do is just
quote a piece of research.

00:12:44.300 --> 00:12:48.260 align:middle line:84%
So for example, if I'm
suggesting to people that what

00:12:48.260 --> 00:12:51.090 align:middle line:84%
they visualize can have a
physical impact in the body,

00:12:51.090 --> 00:12:53.170 align:middle line:84%
now to the mainstream, that
would sound preposterous.

00:12:53.170 --> 00:12:55.610 align:middle line:84%
How can I visualize
myself and change my body?

00:12:55.610 --> 00:12:59.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, here's one part of
many parts of evidence.

00:12:59.530 --> 00:13:02.870 align:middle line:84%
Harvard University did
this fantastic study

00:13:02.870 --> 00:13:06.250 align:middle line:84%
where they asked volunteers
to play a simple combination

00:13:06.250 --> 00:13:06.990 align:middle line:90%
of piano notes.

00:13:06.990 --> 00:13:09.000 align:middle line:84%
So they literally sat
in front of a piano

00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:12.210 align:middle line:84%
and went plunk, plunk,
plunk, plunk repetitively

00:13:12.210 --> 00:13:15.360 align:middle line:84%
for two hours, just five
finger muscle combination,

00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:18.510 align:middle line:84%
repetitively for two hours
on five consecutive days,

00:13:18.510 --> 00:13:20.730 align:middle line:90%
so Monday through Friday.

00:13:20.730 --> 00:13:23.570 align:middle line:84%
And they had their
brain imaged every day.

00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:26.256 align:middle line:84%
And what the scientists
found is that the area

00:13:26.256 --> 00:13:28.550 align:middle line:84%
of the brain connected
to their finger muscles

00:13:28.550 --> 00:13:30.390 align:middle line:90%
began to grow like a muscle.

00:13:30.390 --> 00:13:33.170 align:middle line:84%
And by the fifth day, it
was substantially larger

00:13:33.170 --> 00:13:34.350 align:middle line:90%
than it was on the Monday.

00:13:34.350 --> 00:13:37.210 align:middle line:84%
And that's the term
known as neuroplasticity.

00:13:37.210 --> 00:13:40.180 align:middle line:84%
But where it gets really
interesting is a separate group

00:13:40.180 --> 00:13:42.750 align:middle line:84%
of volunteers, instead
of physical playing

00:13:42.750 --> 00:13:44.920 align:middle line:84%
the piano notes, plunk,
plunk, plunk, plunk,

00:13:44.920 --> 00:13:46.290 align:middle line:90%
they had to do in their heads.

00:13:46.290 --> 00:13:48.660 align:middle line:84%
So they had to just with,
without moving their muscles,

00:13:48.660 --> 00:13:51.390 align:middle line:84%
they had to imagine going plunk,
plunk, plunk, plunk, plunk,

00:13:51.390 --> 00:13:54.330 align:middle line:84%
plunk, repetitively,
for the same two hours

00:13:54.330 --> 00:13:57.300 align:middle line:84%
for the same five consecutive
days, Monday through Friday.

00:13:57.300 --> 00:13:59.560 align:middle line:84%
And they had their
brain imaged every day.

00:13:59.560 --> 00:14:02.270 align:middle line:84%
And incredibly,
their brain began

00:14:02.270 --> 00:14:04.360 align:middle line:84%
to grow like a muscle
in the area connected

00:14:04.360 --> 00:14:05.420 align:middle line:90%
to the finger muscles.

00:14:05.420 --> 00:14:08.350 align:middle line:84%
And if you compared on the
Friday, the brain images

00:14:08.350 --> 00:14:11.500 align:middle line:84%
for those who physically
played the notes with those who

00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:14.260 align:middle line:84%
imagined playing the notes, put
the slides beside each other,

00:14:14.260 --> 00:14:15.670 align:middle line:84%
you couldn't tell
the difference.

00:14:15.670 --> 00:14:17.050 align:middle line:84%
So in other words,
the brain was not

00:14:17.050 --> 00:14:20.220 align:middle line:84%
distinguishing between
who actually played piano

00:14:20.220 --> 00:14:21.440 align:middle line:90%
and who was imagining it.

00:14:21.440 --> 00:14:23.630 align:middle line:84%
So that's a very, very
powerful piece of evidence

00:14:23.630 --> 00:14:26.140 align:middle line:84%
that shows that
we have physically

00:14:26.140 --> 00:14:29.590 align:middle line:84%
shaped the structure of the
brain by imagining something.

00:14:29.590 --> 00:14:32.340 align:middle line:84%
And if we can do that,
what else can we do?

00:14:32.340 --> 00:14:33.980 align:middle line:84%
If we can physically
change-- I mean,

00:14:33.980 --> 00:14:35.140 align:middle line:84%
to change brain
structure, you're

00:14:35.140 --> 00:14:39.470 align:middle line:84%
talking the creation
of hundreds of billions

00:14:39.470 --> 00:14:40.970 align:middle line:90%
of neural connections.

00:14:40.970 --> 00:14:43.900 align:middle line:84%
And a neural connection is
like, if you take two trees

00:14:43.900 --> 00:14:46.940 align:middle line:84%
and hold the roots together,
opposite each other

00:14:46.940 --> 00:14:49.190 align:middle line:84%
and imagine the roots were
growing towards each other,

00:14:49.190 --> 00:14:51.220 align:middle line:84%
you're talking
hundreds of billions

00:14:51.220 --> 00:14:54.990 align:middle line:84%
of brand new roots being created
seemingly out of thin air,

00:14:54.990 --> 00:14:55.690 align:middle line:90%
but not really.

00:14:55.690 --> 00:14:58.770 align:middle line:84%
There's a little domino
effect from the impact

00:14:58.770 --> 00:15:01.030 align:middle line:90%
of your imagining on your genes.

00:15:01.030 --> 00:15:03.190 align:middle line:84%
At the genetic level, there's a
whole domino effect that starts

00:15:03.190 --> 00:15:04.790 align:middle line:90%
to construct these connections.

00:15:04.790 --> 00:15:07.730 align:middle line:84%
But this is occurring because
of something you're imagining,

00:15:07.730 --> 00:15:09.310 align:middle line:90%
not something you're doing.

00:15:09.310 --> 00:15:11.430 align:middle line:84%
So when I present that
kind of evidence to people

00:15:11.430 --> 00:15:13.880 align:middle line:84%
and it's published in a top
level mainstream journal,

00:15:13.880 --> 00:15:17.890 align:middle line:84%
it's hard to then have any
argument against that the mind

00:15:17.890 --> 00:15:18.650 align:middle line:90%
has this effect on.

00:15:18.650 --> 00:15:21.910 align:middle line:90%
The body

00:15:21.910 --> 00:15:24.190 align:middle line:84%
What part of the
brain actually?

00:15:24.190 --> 00:15:25.170 align:middle line:90%
How do you see it?

00:15:25.170 --> 00:15:29.880 align:middle line:84%
How can you see that's it's
growing, it's connecting?

00:15:29.880 --> 00:15:32.400 align:middle line:84%
There are several brain
imaging techniques.

00:15:32.400 --> 00:15:35.510 align:middle line:84%
In this piano study,
they used a technique

00:15:35.510 --> 00:15:37.980 align:middle line:84%
called transcranial
magnetic stimulation.

00:15:37.980 --> 00:15:40.650 align:middle line:84%
Most people have
heard of MRI and PET.

00:15:40.650 --> 00:15:42.690 align:middle line:84%
TMS, transcranial
magnetic stimulation,

00:15:42.690 --> 00:15:44.860 align:middle line:84%
is just a way of imaging
the brain by fighting bolts

00:15:44.860 --> 00:15:47.140 align:middle line:84%
of magnetic pulses
into it and you can get

00:15:47.140 --> 00:15:49.210 align:middle line:90%
a picture of what's going on.

00:15:49.210 --> 00:15:52.790 align:middle line:84%
And what they find is the area
of the brain begins to grow,

00:15:52.790 --> 00:15:54.930 align:middle line:84%
but it's the area connected
to the finger muscles

00:15:54.930 --> 00:15:57.240 align:middle line:84%
because you're imagining
your finger muscles growing.

00:15:57.240 --> 00:15:58.460 align:middle line:90%
Which area of the brain?

00:15:58.460 --> 00:15:59.330 align:middle line:90%
How do you know?

00:15:59.330 --> 00:16:00.130 align:middle line:90%
It's right across here.

00:16:00.130 --> 00:16:01.660 align:middle line:90%
It's called the motor cortex.

00:16:01.660 --> 00:16:04.050 align:middle line:84%
It runs right across the
top of the head here.

00:16:04.050 --> 00:16:08.615 align:middle line:84%
And actually it's shaped --
it's called the homunculus.

00:16:08.615 --> 00:16:11.540 align:middle line:84%
A homunculus is like a
reflexology maps, right?

00:16:11.540 --> 00:16:14.190 align:middle line:84%
You look at a reflexology
map of the foot

00:16:14.190 --> 00:16:16.000 align:middle line:84%
and you see there's
a bit for the liver,

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:17.510 align:middle line:90%
the kidneys, and all that.

00:16:17.510 --> 00:16:19.520 align:middle line:84%
Well, in the brain it's
referred to as a homunculus.

00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:23.510 align:middle line:84%
So it's like the whole body part
is compressed into the strip.

00:16:23.510 --> 00:16:27.060 align:middle line:84%
And so there's a different
part for your little finger.

00:16:27.060 --> 00:16:28.530 align:middle line:84%
There's a different
part for you big toe.

00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:31.180 align:middle line:84%
There's a part for your ear,
your nose, your buttock.

00:16:31.180 --> 00:16:34.020 align:middle line:84%
Up So when you
place your attention

00:16:34.020 --> 00:16:35.350 align:middle line:84%
on any part of
the body, in fact,

00:16:35.350 --> 00:16:38.220 align:middle line:84%
this was done at the
Karolinska Institute

00:16:38.220 --> 00:16:40.520 align:middle line:84%
in Sweden, which is one of
the most famous institutes

00:16:40.520 --> 00:16:43.060 align:middle line:84%
in the world because
Nobel Prize winners give

00:16:43.060 --> 00:16:46.780 align:middle line:84%
Nobel lectures there in
medicine and physiology.

00:16:46.780 --> 00:16:49.090 align:middle line:84%
And they found that if you
just put your attention

00:16:49.090 --> 00:16:52.290 align:middle line:84%
on your tongue or on your finger
or another part of your body,

00:16:52.290 --> 00:16:55.810 align:middle line:84%
you activate selectively the
part of the reflexology map

00:16:55.810 --> 00:16:57.990 align:middle line:84%
or homunculus as it's
known in the brain,

00:16:57.990 --> 00:17:01.030 align:middle line:84%
you specifically activate that
part and not the other parts,

00:17:01.030 --> 00:17:03.840 align:middle line:84%
just where your
attention is focused.

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:06.460 align:middle line:84%
And in the mind body
spirit field for years,

00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:08.839 align:middle line:84%
people have said energy
flows where attention goes.

00:17:08.839 --> 00:17:11.140 align:middle line:84%
Well, in a real
neurological sense,

00:17:11.140 --> 00:17:13.450 align:middle line:84%
we now have the evidence that
if you place your attention,

00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:15.720 align:middle line:84%
there is certainly activation
in the brain and a current

00:17:15.720 --> 00:17:18.760 align:middle line:84%
of electricity that
stimulates the specific area,

00:17:18.760 --> 00:17:20.869 align:middle line:84%
even if it's the
tip of your finger.

00:17:20.869 --> 00:17:22.950 align:middle line:84%
So when the people
did the piano study

00:17:22.950 --> 00:17:28.450 align:middle line:84%
they found that the
specific finger muscles,

00:17:28.450 --> 00:17:30.630 align:middle line:84%
those specific parts of the
brain and everywhere else,

00:17:30.630 --> 00:17:34.520 align:middle line:84%
just those parts began
to grow like a muscle.

00:17:34.520 --> 00:17:35.600 align:middle line:90%
This is fascinating.

00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:38.200 align:middle line:90%
I love hearing those.

00:17:38.200 --> 00:17:41.320 align:middle line:84%
So one of the questions that
now runs through my mind

00:17:41.320 --> 00:17:44.050 align:middle line:84%
is that a lot of
scientific00 or we

00:17:44.050 --> 00:17:47.400 align:middle line:84%
hear a lot to talk about
our left and right brain.

00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:50.450 align:middle line:84%
