Absolutely.

00:18:07.360 --> 00:18:09.990 align:middle line:84%
And then the more we allow
ourselves to feel our emotions

00:18:09.990 --> 00:18:12.290 align:middle line:84%
and express our
emotions-- I'm sitting

00:18:12.290 --> 00:18:14.500 align:middle line:90%
here in a hotel in Scotland.

00:18:14.500 --> 00:18:16.470 align:middle line:84%
And when I grew up in
Scotland, showing your emotions

00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:18.180 align:middle line:90%
was not a big thing.

00:18:18.180 --> 00:18:22.300 align:middle line:84%
So I personally grew up-- I
worked as a scientist for years

00:18:22.300 --> 00:18:23.930 align:middle line:84%
in the lab and I
still had difficulty

00:18:23.930 --> 00:18:28.100 align:middle line:84%
showing emotion because it's
embarrassing, for men like me.

00:18:28.100 --> 00:18:30.180 align:middle line:84%
It's embarrassing
according to our culture

00:18:30.180 --> 00:18:31.510 align:middle line:90%
so I would never do it.

00:18:31.510 --> 00:18:33.910 align:middle line:84%
And it has taken me a
decade since leaving

00:18:33.910 --> 00:18:35.020 align:middle line:90%
the pharmaceutical industry.

00:18:35.020 --> 00:18:37.150 align:middle line:84%
And now I've gotten so
far to the other side,

00:18:37.150 --> 00:18:40.480 align:middle line:84%
that I watch anything that's
slightly emotional on TV

00:18:40.480 --> 00:18:42.420 align:middle line:90%
