00:18:56.130 --> 00:19:00.120 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's a consequence
of me using my creative side.

00:19:00.120 --> 00:19:02.430 align:middle line:84%
Because in the lab it
was just analytical, just

00:19:02.430 --> 00:19:03.630 align:middle line:90%
left brain the whole time.

00:19:03.630 --> 00:19:07.230 align:middle line:84%
And as I left there and
started to research other stuff

00:19:07.230 --> 00:19:09.780 align:middle line:84%
and visualize stuff,
the more you visualize,

00:19:09.780 --> 00:19:11.410 align:middle line:84%
you start to use
the right brain.

00:19:11.410 --> 00:19:13.640 align:middle line:84%
And what's begun
to happen is it's

00:19:13.640 --> 00:19:16.540 align:middle line:84%
allowed me to express and feel
emotion in a much deeper way

00:19:16.540 --> 00:19:17.840 align:middle line:90%
than ever before.

00:19:17.840 --> 00:19:19.600 align:middle line:84%
But what it also
does is, because I'm

00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:23.180 align:middle line:84%
using the left and the right,
analytical and the imaginative,

00:19:23.180 --> 00:19:25.330 align:middle line:84%
the creativity part
of it, it integrates

00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:26.400 align:middle line:90%
both hemispheres together.

00:19:26.400 --> 00:19:29.510 align:middle line:84%
And we end up with far more
brain capacity, brainpower,

00:19:29.510 --> 00:19:33.760 align:middle line:84%
much clearer, sharper in your
mind than ever I was before.

00:19:33.760 --> 00:19:35.150 align:middle line:84%
I thought I was
really bright, really

00:19:35.150 --> 00:19:37.880 align:middle line:90%
clever when I was a scientist.

00:19:37.880 --> 00:19:41.544 align:middle line:84%
But I'm light years beyond
where I was a decade ago.

00:19:41.544 --> 00:19:46.490 align:middle line:84%
A lot of scientific are right
now stuck in their equations

00:19:46.490 --> 00:19:48.140 align:middle line:90%
and in papers that are there.

00:19:48.140 --> 00:19:52.080 align:middle line:84%
And from a lot of interviews
that I'm doing a lot of people

00:19:52.080 --> 00:19:53.840 align:middle line:84%
speak about stepping
in the unknown

00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:58.310 align:middle line:84%
and there is some scientists
that have stepped in there.

00:19:58.310 --> 00:20:00.880 align:middle line:84%
It's called quantum
physics, I guess, small more

00:20:00.880 --> 00:20:04.540 align:middle line:84%
in that field, where
you just go into a much

00:20:04.540 --> 00:20:06.690 align:middle line:90%
larger scope of life.

00:20:06.690 --> 00:20:08.790 align:middle line:84%
And it seems like this
is where it's heading.

00:20:08.790 --> 00:20:11.740 align:middle line:84%
Now, you speak of
quantum entanglement

00:20:11.740 --> 00:20:13.540 align:middle line:90%
and all kinds of things now.

00:20:13.540 --> 00:20:15.820 align:middle line:84%
So it's backed up
by this new science.

00:20:15.820 --> 00:20:17.200 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:20:17.200 --> 00:20:18.500 align:middle line:90%
This is so fascinating.

00:20:18.500 --> 00:20:21.040 align:middle line:84%
See if you were to look
inside any part of your body.

00:20:21.040 --> 00:20:23.760 align:middle line:84%
So I could look inside
my hand, and if you

00:20:23.760 --> 00:20:25.570 align:middle line:84%
look inside your
hand, you get cells.

00:20:25.570 --> 00:20:28.190 align:middle line:84%
But look inside my
cells, you find your DNA,

00:20:28.190 --> 00:20:30.440 align:middle line:90%
proteins, enzymes, hormones.

00:20:30.440 --> 00:20:32.010 align:middle line:84%
And you look inside
them, and you

00:20:32.010 --> 00:20:35.730 align:middle line:84%
find they're made of atoms,
carbons, hydrogens, oxygen,

00:20:35.730 --> 00:20:37.250 align:middle line:90%
nitrogen, sulfur, phosphorus.

00:20:37.250 --> 00:20:41.040 align:middle line:84%
You look inside an atom
and there's nothing there.

00:20:41.040 --> 00:20:42.140 align:middle line:90%
Almost nothing.

00:20:42.140 --> 00:20:45.480 align:middle line:84%
You have protons, neutrons, and
electrons croutons and morons.

00:20:45.480 --> 00:20:46.285 align:middle line:90%
No, you don't.

00:20:46.285 --> 00:20:47.500 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:20:47.500 --> 00:20:49.150 align:middle line:84%
No, you don't really
have croutons and morons.

00:20:49.150 --> 00:20:54.070 align:middle line:84%
But there should be croutons,
because the Large Hadron

00:20:54.070 --> 00:20:57.770 align:middle line:84%
Collider in Switzerland has
been smashing particles together

00:20:57.770 --> 00:20:59.670 align:middle line:84%
and all the fragments
that come out of it

00:20:59.670 --> 00:21:01.340 align:middle line:90%
are known as a quantum soup.

00:21:01.340 --> 00:21:04.400 align:middle line:84%
So I think there should be
croutons, just not name it yet.

00:21:04.400 --> 00:21:06.150 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, protons,
neutrons, and electrons.

00:21:06.150 --> 00:21:09.420 align:middle line:84%
And what's amazing, is
inside an atom there is

00:21:09.420 --> 00:21:15.770 align:middle line:90%
99.9999999999999% empty space.

00:21:15.770 --> 00:21:19.240 align:middle line:84%
That's 13 nines percent
empty space inside an atom.

00:21:19.240 --> 00:21:21.810 align:middle line:84%
If a proton was the
size of a grape,

00:21:21.810 --> 00:21:23.490 align:middle line:84%
like a grape that
you make wine out of,

00:21:23.490 --> 00:21:25.180 align:middle line:84%
if a proton was the
size of a grape,

00:21:25.180 --> 00:21:29.250 align:middle line:84%
the closest electron would be
the size of a particle of dust.

00:21:29.250 --> 00:21:31.720 align:middle line:84%
And it would be
approximately two miles away.

00:21:31.720 --> 00:21:34.790 align:middle line:84%
So think for the moment how
far two miles is from her.

00:21:34.790 --> 00:21:37.780 align:middle line:84%
And imagine I have a grape in
my hand and that's a proton.

00:21:37.780 --> 00:21:40.090 align:middle line:84%
The closest electron
is two miles away

00:21:40.090 --> 00:21:41.470 align:middle line:90%
and it's now buzzing around.

00:21:41.470 --> 00:21:44.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's a reality inside
every atom in the body.

00:21:44.890 --> 00:21:47.240 align:middle line:84%
And there are
countless, trillions,

00:21:47.240 --> 00:21:49.920 align:middle line:84%
trillions and trillions
and godzillions

00:21:49.920 --> 00:21:51.650 align:middle line:90%
of atoms inside the body.

00:21:51.650 --> 00:21:54.475 align:middle line:84%
But one of the
interest phenomena

00:21:54.475 --> 00:21:56.870 align:middle line:84%
that you begin to observe when
you get to the quantum level.

00:21:56.870 --> 00:21:58.170 align:middle line:84%
In fact, you look
inside a proton

00:21:58.170 --> 00:22:01.260 align:middle line:84%
and there's three quarks, two
up quarks and a down quark.

00:22:01.260 --> 00:22:03.030 align:middle line:84%
And when you get to
this kind of level,

00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:06.100 align:middle line:84%
you find that all of the
particles are interconnected.

00:22:06.100 --> 00:22:08.580 align:middle line:84%
And scientist call
that entanglement.

00:22:08.580 --> 00:22:10.700 align:middle line:84%
And most cosmologists
would now agree

00:22:10.700 --> 00:22:12.690 align:middle line:84%
that the birth of the
universe, every particle

00:22:12.690 --> 00:22:14.190 align:middle line:90%
was connected at one point.

00:22:14.190 --> 00:22:17.480 align:middle line:84%
So therefore on some
level, the entire universe

00:22:17.480 --> 00:22:18.750 align:middle line:90%
is now entangled.

00:22:18.750 --> 00:22:23.190 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is that
the particles, the protons

00:22:23.190 --> 00:22:27.640 align:middle line:84%
inside your body right now are
connected to protons in a leaf

00:22:27.640 --> 00:22:29.190 align:middle line:84%
on a tree in the
Amazon rainforest,

00:22:29.190 --> 00:22:34.110 align:middle line:84%
which are connected to electrons
in the outermost portions

00:22:34.110 --> 00:22:36.140 align:middle line:84%
of a distant galaxy
a trillion trillion

00:22:36.140 --> 00:22:37.880 align:middle line:90%
billion light years from here.

00:22:37.880 --> 00:22:39.020 align:middle line:90%
And everything's interconnected.

00:22:39.020 --> 00:22:42.830 align:middle line:84%
What's really interesting
is on some level,

00:22:42.830 --> 00:22:44.410 align:middle line:84%
you have types of
particles called fermions

00:22:44.410 --> 00:22:46.540 align:middle line:84%
and no two fermions
can be the same state.

00:22:46.540 --> 00:22:49.820 align:middle line:84%
So on one level,
as you just think,

00:22:49.820 --> 00:22:51.960 align:middle line:84%
as you think, and you
shape you brain chemistry,

00:22:51.960 --> 00:22:55.770 align:middle line:84%
that changes the temperature
of the atoms in the vicinity.

00:22:55.770 --> 00:22:58.170 align:middle line:84%
And what that does is it
puts certain particles

00:22:58.170 --> 00:22:59.410 align:middle line:90%
into a particular state.

00:22:59.410 --> 00:23:01.950 align:middle line:84%
But what this means if no
two particles of this type

00:23:01.950 --> 00:23:03.530 align:middle line:90%
can be in the same state.

00:23:03.530 --> 00:23:06.130 align:middle line:84%
It means on some level
the entire universe

00:23:06.130 --> 00:23:09.180 align:middle line:84%
has to agree with what
you're thinking about.

00:23:09.180 --> 00:23:13.040 align:middle line:84%
The entire universe must know
on some weird level what you're

00:23:13.040 --> 00:23:16.210 align:middle line:84%
doing, otherwise
there's a possibility

00:23:16.210 --> 00:23:18.230 align:middle line:84%
that another particle
can be the same state.

00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:20.240 align:middle line:84%
But that's not allowed by
the rules of quantum physics.

00:23:20.240 --> 00:23:23.530 align:middle line:84%
So on some level the
entire universe must know,

00:23:23.530 --> 00:23:26.350 align:middle line:84%
it must be somehow
aware of everything

00:23:26.350 --> 00:23:27.890 align:middle line:90%
that's going on right now.

00:23:27.890 --> 00:23:30.970 align:middle line:84%
Which then brings us to the
cause and effect, which means

00:23:30.970 --> 00:23:33.060 align:middle line:84%
that every time we
change a decision,

00:23:33.060 --> 00:23:37.360 align:middle line:84%
it has an effect on the
future and on others

00:23:37.360 --> 00:23:39.610 align:middle line:90%
lives, our planet.

00:23:39.610 --> 00:23:40.430 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:23:40.430 --> 00:23:43.510 align:middle line:84%
In fact, one of the
challenges mainstream

00:23:43.510 --> 00:23:47.370 align:middle line:84%
physicists often present when
people in the spiritual mind

00:23:47.370 --> 00:23:50.340 align:middle line:84%
body spirit field talk
about entanglement,

00:23:50.340 --> 00:23:53.570 align:middle line:84%
physicists use the argument
that you can't exactly

00:23:53.570 --> 00:23:57.190 align:middle line:84%
send a message from one
particle to another, like a text

00:23:57.190 --> 00:23:58.270 align:middle line:90%
message kind of thing.

00:23:58.270 --> 00:24:00.890 align:middle line:84%
But what we're
beginning to understand

00:24:00.890 --> 00:24:03.730 align:middle line:84%
is if you go even
deeper, there's

00:24:03.730 --> 00:24:05.290 align:middle line:84%
a growing body of
scientists, including

00:24:05.290 --> 00:24:08.331 align:middle line:84%
myself, who would suggest
that the universe isn't inept.

00:24:08.331 --> 00:24:09.030 align:middle line:90%
It's not dead.

00:24:09.030 --> 00:24:11.760 align:middle line:84%
It's not random fluctuations
in the quantum field

00:24:11.760 --> 00:24:13.910 align:middle line:84%
that create the
quarks, but perhaps

00:24:13.910 --> 00:24:19.400 align:middle line:84%
at the deepest fabric of reality
itself, the universe is alive.

00:24:19.400 --> 00:24:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And as preposterous as that may
sound to mainstream, by making

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:25.720 align:middle line:84%
that assumption is
one of the only ways

00:24:25.720 --> 00:24:29.150 align:middle line:84%
you can start to understand some
of the experiments that show

00:24:29.150 --> 00:24:31.740 align:middle line:84%
that if one person--
take a couple who

00:24:31.740 --> 00:24:34.730 align:middle line:84%
share a strong emotional
bond, typical experiment.

00:24:34.730 --> 00:24:36.540 align:middle line:84%
And you put you separate
them by a distance.

00:24:36.540 --> 00:24:40.070 align:middle line:84%
Put one inside an MRI scanner,
the other down the corridor.

00:24:40.070 --> 00:24:42.980 align:middle line:84%
And you flash a light in
the eyes of the one down

00:24:42.980 --> 00:24:45.330 align:middle line:84%
the corridor, but because
they're emotionally connected,

00:24:45.330 --> 00:24:47.500 align:middle line:84%
what you find in
the MRI it picks up

00:24:47.500 --> 00:24:49.860 align:middle line:84%
a flash in the visual
cortex-- that's

00:24:49.860 --> 00:24:53.010 align:middle line:84%
the area that processes visual
information --in their partner.

00:24:53.010 --> 00:24:56.910 align:middle line:84%
So one person saw something,
but their partner's brain

00:24:56.910 --> 00:24:57.910 align:middle line:90%
thought they saw it.

00:24:57.910 --> 00:25:00.280 align:middle line:84%
And this is separated
by a distance.

00:25:00.280 --> 00:25:03.400 align:middle line:84%
And the only way you can
account for that is by the idea

00:25:03.400 --> 00:25:06.700 align:middle line:84%
that your consciousness
isn't inside your head.

00:25:06.700 --> 00:25:08.700 align:middle line:84%
It's not produced
by brain chemistry,

00:25:08.700 --> 00:25:10.110 align:middle line:90%
which is the mainstream view.

00:25:10.110 --> 00:25:12.950 align:middle line:84%
And you start to then
arrive at a conclusion.

00:25:12.950 --> 00:25:14.720 align:middle line:84%
The only logical
conclusion is maybe

00:25:14.720 --> 00:25:19.540 align:middle line:84%
consciousness is something more
fundamental to reality itself.

00:25:19.540 --> 00:25:21.210 align:middle line:84%
And if you take
that assumption, it

00:25:21.210 --> 00:25:23.580 align:middle line:84%
means there's consciousness
in everything, even

00:25:23.580 --> 00:25:25.890 align:middle line:84%
in a blade of grass,
even a leaf on a tree

00:25:25.890 --> 00:25:28.870 align:middle line:84%
and a piece of bark on a
tree, even a piece of stone

00:25:28.870 --> 00:25:30.570 align:middle line:90%
that you walk on.

00:25:30.570 --> 00:25:32.800 align:middle line:84%
I'm not suggesting it's
self aware consciousness.

00:25:32.800 --> 00:25:36.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean my table at home doesn't
sit up late at night to watch

00:25:36.200 --> 00:25:39.400 align:middle line:90%
"Star Trek" with excitement.

00:25:39.400 --> 00:25:43.150 align:middle line:84%
But there must be like a
background hum of consciousness

00:25:43.150 --> 00:25:44.050 align:middle line:90%
in every single thing.

00:25:44.050 --> 00:25:46.420 align:middle line:84%
You probably require a neural
net in the brain to have

00:25:46.420 --> 00:25:47.780 align:middle line:90%
of our type of consciousness.

00:25:47.780 --> 00:25:50.750 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't include a
consciousness in everything.

00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:52.740 align:middle line:84%
And so when you start
to look into the deepest

00:25:52.740 --> 00:25:55.565 align:middle line:84%
fabric of reality, you start
to arrive at the conclusion

00:25:55.565 --> 00:25:58.720 align:middle line:84%
that perhaps it's
alive and therefore

00:25:58.720 --> 00:26:00.690 align:middle line:90%
everything is interconnected.

00:26:00.690 --> 00:26:02.130 align:middle line:84%
And this idea that
you can't send

00:26:02.130 --> 00:26:04.200 align:middle line:84%
a text message, maybe
that only relates

00:26:04.200 --> 00:26:05.215 align:middle line:90%
to protons and electrons.

00:26:05.215 --> 00:26:08.650 align:middle line:84%
But when you go Even deeper to
basic fabric of reality, then

00:26:08.650 --> 00:26:10.370 align:middle line:84%
perhaps we're
constantly exchanging

00:26:10.370 --> 00:26:13.020 align:middle line:84%
information, conscious
transformation,

00:26:13.020 --> 00:26:14.730 align:middle line:90%
with the entire universe.

00:26:14.730 --> 00:26:16.640 align:middle line:84%
And I really believe
that happens.

00:26:16.640 --> 00:26:18.630 align:middle line:84%
And these types
of MRI experiments

00:26:18.630 --> 00:26:21.510 align:middle line:84%
are beginning to
suggest that that might

00:26:21.510 --> 00:26:23.900 align:middle line:90%
really be how things work.

