00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:27.170 align:middle line:90%
dropped the pebble in the pond.

00:27:27.170 --> 00:27:29.640 align:middle line:90%
So that's the metaphor I guess.

00:27:29.640 --> 00:27:32.140 align:middle line:84%
And the pebble in the
pond is a single thought

00:27:32.140 --> 00:27:34.110 align:middle line:84%
of kindness and
love and compassion

00:27:34.110 --> 00:27:38.010 align:middle line:84%
that sends these ripples that
go on for infinity, infinity.

00:27:38.010 --> 00:27:41.350 align:middle line:84%
So you start to feel
more empowered then.

00:27:41.350 --> 00:27:45.120 align:middle line:84%
You start to understand that
maybe I can impact the world.

00:27:45.120 --> 00:27:47.460 align:middle line:84%
And it really just
starts in my own mind.

00:27:47.460 --> 00:27:50.950 align:middle line:84%
And it's doing away with this
idea that we're powerless

00:27:50.950 --> 00:27:54.000 align:middle line:84%
and replacing it with this
idea of being powerful.

00:27:54.000 --> 00:27:55.460 align:middle line:84%
And that our thoughts
really carry.

00:27:55.460 --> 00:27:58.620 align:middle line:84%
They're not floaty, inert things
that disappear into the ether,

00:27:58.620 --> 00:28:00.810 align:middle line:84%
but they always
have consequences.

00:28:00.810 --> 00:28:03.305 align:middle line:84%
So therefore, you're led to
the inevitable conclusion

00:28:03.305 --> 00:28:07.590 align:middle line:84%
that if I'm so powerful it
matters what I think about.

00:28:07.590 --> 00:28:10.490 align:middle line:84%
So therefore if you want to
make the world a better place,

00:28:10.490 --> 00:28:14.970 align:middle line:84%
then start it in your mind more
with ideas of gratitude, ideas

00:28:14.970 --> 00:28:17.590 align:middle line:84%
of compassion and kindness and
think of people in the best

00:28:17.590 --> 00:28:20.870 align:middle line:84%
possible sense, instead of
dwelling on the stuff that's

00:28:20.870 --> 00:28:23.510 align:middle line:84%
annoying, dwelling on the people
that we don't get on with,

00:28:23.510 --> 00:28:25.670 align:middle line:84%
dwelling on stressful
thing, dwelling on what's

00:28:25.670 --> 00:28:27.030 align:middle line:90%
not working in our lives.

00:28:27.030 --> 00:28:29.810 align:middle line:84%
And start to focus on
the magic, on the beauty,

00:28:29.810 --> 00:28:31.830 align:middle line:90%
on the specialness of life.

00:28:31.830 --> 00:28:34.290 align:middle line:84%
And you send this
ripple out that it does

00:28:34.290 --> 00:28:36.350 align:middle line:90%
eventually impact the world.

00:28:36.350 --> 00:28:37.990 align:middle line:84%
Because if many of us
think the same way,

00:28:37.990 --> 00:28:40.366 align:middle line:90%
then the world can only change.

00:28:40.366 --> 00:28:42.540 align:middle line:84%
Because we want to see
immediate results too.

00:28:42.540 --> 00:28:44.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean this is part
of our society.

00:28:44.400 --> 00:28:45.720 align:middle line:90%
We want to see right now.

00:28:45.720 --> 00:28:47.920 align:middle line:84%
So those thoughts
unfortunately, we

00:28:47.920 --> 00:28:51.280 align:middle line:84%
don't know immediately the
impact that it will have,

00:28:51.280 --> 00:28:53.430 align:middle line:84%
even if we meditate
10 minutes a day

00:28:53.430 --> 00:28:55.340 align:middle line:84%
or if we have
these good thoughts

00:28:55.340 --> 00:28:57.710 align:middle line:84%
and make those
declaration or intentions,

00:28:57.710 --> 00:28:59.970 align:middle line:84%
sometimes you don't see it
right away and we give up.

00:28:59.970 --> 00:29:01.240 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:29:01.240 --> 00:29:04.220 align:middle line:84%
It's so common to give
up because we're looking

00:29:04.220 --> 00:29:05.310 align:middle line:90%
for these immediate results.

00:29:05.310 --> 00:29:07.685 align:middle line:84%
So if you're thinking doesn't
have an immediate result,

00:29:07.685 --> 00:29:09.860 align:middle line:84%
not only do we give
up, but we start

00:29:09.860 --> 00:29:12.400 align:middle line:90%
to feel that I have no power.

00:29:12.400 --> 00:29:15.440 align:middle line:84%
We start to feel, surely I've
been thinking of that thing

00:29:15.440 --> 00:29:16.580 align:middle line:90%
and nothing's happened.

00:29:16.580 --> 00:29:18.595 align:middle line:84%
I haven't changed the
world with a single thought

00:29:18.595 --> 00:29:20.120 align:middle line:90%
so I must not be good at this.

00:29:20.120 --> 00:29:21.330 align:middle line:90%
And we disempower ourselves.

00:29:21.330 --> 00:29:25.830 align:middle line:84%
But if we can replace that need
for immediacy with the idea

00:29:25.830 --> 00:29:27.670 align:middle line:90%
that there's a bit a lag time.

00:29:27.670 --> 00:29:29.830 align:middle line:84%
It's like if a
person is painting

00:29:29.830 --> 00:29:32.930 align:middle line:84%
watercolor, to create an image
you have to do several washes.

00:29:32.930 --> 00:29:35.045 align:middle line:84%
So you wash over another
wash, another wash,

00:29:35.045 --> 00:29:38.094 align:middle line:84%
and gradually the image gets
darker and darker and darker,

00:29:38.094 --> 00:29:38.860 align:middle line:90%
until it's really real.

00:29:38.860 --> 00:29:42.410 align:middle line:84%
And I think to use that kind
of metaphor, that to begin

00:29:42.410 --> 00:29:44.540 align:middle line:84%
to shape life in
a significant way,

00:29:44.540 --> 00:29:47.370 align:middle line:84%
we have to repeat
the same thought.

00:29:47.370 --> 00:29:51.690 align:middle line:84%
It' like the piano study
the neuroplasticity study

00:29:51.690 --> 00:29:54.150 align:middle line:84%
in the brain, we didn't
shape brain circuits

00:29:54.150 --> 00:29:57.320 align:middle line:84%
by just imagining playing
the piano notes once.

00:29:57.320 --> 00:29:59.350 align:middle line:84%
We had to do the same
thing repetitively.

00:29:59.350 --> 00:30:03.320 align:middle line:84%
So maybe if we
understand that sometimes

00:30:03.320 --> 00:30:05.080 align:middle line:84%
things will shift
with just one idea.

00:30:05.080 --> 00:30:06.980 align:middle line:84%
But many times for
the average person

00:30:06.980 --> 00:30:09.900 align:middle line:84%
it takes thinking the
same thing several times.

00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:11.960 align:middle line:84%
And that begins to build
patience because if we

00:30:11.960 --> 00:30:14.220 align:middle line:84%
understand that's
probably how it works,

00:30:14.220 --> 00:30:16.750 align:middle line:84%
then we stop looking
for immediate results.

00:30:16.750 --> 00:30:19.150 align:middle line:84%
When they come immediately,
whoa, it's a blessing.

00:30:19.150 --> 00:30:21.240 align:middle line:84%
But we don't need to
have immediate results.

00:30:21.240 --> 00:30:24.790 align:middle line:84%
So therefore we maintain
the sense of being powerful.

00:30:24.790 --> 00:30:26.200 align:middle line:90%
You used to coach athletes?

00:30:26.200 --> 00:30:27.610 align:middle line:90%
Do you still do it.

00:30:27.610 --> 00:30:28.920 align:middle line:90%
I don't formally anymore.

00:30:28.920 --> 00:30:30.720 align:middle line:90%
I give pieces of advice, yeah.

00:30:30.720 --> 00:30:32.430 align:middle line:84%
But while I worked
as a scientist,

00:30:32.430 --> 00:30:37.850 align:middle line:84%
I was an athletics coach, I
coached long jump, triple jump.

00:30:37.850 --> 00:30:40.080 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting, the
power of visualization,

00:30:40.080 --> 00:30:41.500 align:middle line:90%
they use it a lot.

00:30:41.500 --> 00:30:44.000 align:middle line:90%
Athletes do have coaches.

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:47.150 align:middle line:84%
And I spoke-- and a friend
of mine is Lewis Pugh.

00:30:47.150 --> 00:30:51.190 align:middle line:84%
So he's a British athlete
and mentalist that

00:30:51.190 --> 00:30:53.120 align:middle line:90%
swim across the North Pole.

00:30:53.120 --> 00:30:57.140 align:middle line:84%
And he said, 2/3 of my work
has been visualizing the cold

00:30:57.140 --> 00:31:01.040 align:middle line:84%
of the water and going
through until he was ready

00:31:01.040 --> 00:31:03.950 align:middle line:84%
and then just being in the
water, he was prepared.

00:31:03.950 --> 00:31:05.500 align:middle line:90%
Yeah absolutely.

00:31:05.500 --> 00:31:06.870 align:middle line:84%
When I was an
athletics coach, you

00:31:06.870 --> 00:31:10.590 align:middle line:84%
start to understand that the
top athletes in the world, they

00:31:10.590 --> 00:31:12.100 align:middle line:90%
all use visualization.

00:31:12.100 --> 00:31:14.740 align:middle line:84%
In fact, Usain Bolt, when
he broke the 100 meters

00:31:14.740 --> 00:31:18.100 align:middle line:84%
world record a few
years ago, he ran 9.58.

00:31:18.100 --> 00:31:22.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a preposterously fast
time, awesomely fast time.

00:31:22.180 --> 00:31:24.910 align:middle line:84%
And he was quoted at
the end as saying,

00:31:24.910 --> 00:31:28.700 align:middle line:84%
I just visualized
and then run my race.

00:31:28.700 --> 00:31:31.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's just a fragment of
the volume of virtualization

00:31:31.790 --> 00:31:33.510 align:middle line:90%
that athletes actually do.

00:31:33.510 --> 00:31:36.090 align:middle line:84%
Because of athlete visualize
themselves like swimming,

00:31:36.090 --> 00:31:39.330 align:middle line:84%
for your friend for example,
then the brain processes

00:31:39.330 --> 00:31:41.010 align:middle line:90%
as if it's actually happening.

00:31:41.010 --> 00:31:42.470 align:middle line:84%
So if he's imagining
swimming in really,

00:31:42.470 --> 00:31:45.330 align:middle line:84%
really cold, then the brain
is processing it as if he can

00:31:45.330 --> 00:31:46.470 align:middle line:90%
swim in really, really cool.

00:31:46.470 --> 00:31:48.340 align:middle line:84%
So the brain begins to
alter it's chemistry,

00:31:48.340 --> 00:31:51.290 align:middle line:84%
alter the biological
processes in the body that

00:31:51.290 --> 00:31:53.360 align:middle line:90%
allow him to swim in the cold.

00:31:53.360 --> 00:31:57.510 align:middle line:84%
And for an athlete who's jumping
or hurdling or sprinting,

00:31:57.510 --> 00:31:59.580 align:middle line:84%
then the conditions in which
they imagine themselves

00:31:59.580 --> 00:32:02.640 align:middle line:84%
performing, the brain begins
to alter the chemical processes

00:32:02.640 --> 00:32:05.110 align:middle line:84%
in the body so that the
body is able to do the thing

00:32:05.110 --> 00:32:07.500 align:middle line:90%
that your imagine it doing.

00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:08.710 align:middle line:90%
What a beautiful machine.

00:32:08.710 --> 00:32:11.270 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, a beautiful
machine that we are.

00:32:11.270 --> 00:32:13.860 align:middle line:84%
Yeah. we're far more
than we think we are.

00:32:13.860 --> 00:32:16.430 align:middle line:90%
The impossible seems possible.

00:32:16.430 --> 00:32:19.430 align:middle line:84%
I think we're capable of
so much more than we think.

00:32:19.430 --> 00:32:22.610 align:middle line:84%
I never cease to be
amazed at the capacity

00:32:22.610 --> 00:32:24.850 align:middle line:84%
people have to
heal their bodies,

00:32:24.850 --> 00:32:28.870 align:middle line:84%
perform great feats of
strength and endurance

00:32:28.870 --> 00:32:31.230 align:middle line:84%
or to shape the
circumstances of our life,

00:32:31.230 --> 00:32:34.180 align:middle line:84%
even when they've been in
really challenging situations.

00:32:34.180 --> 00:32:36.400 align:middle line:84%
It's important to talk
also in this conversation

00:32:36.400 --> 00:32:40.530 align:middle line:84%
about negative feelings or
about belief system that

00:32:40.530 --> 00:32:42.140 align:middle line:90%
are stuck in the subconscious.

00:32:42.140 --> 00:32:44.100 align:middle line:84%
Now it's a big part
of how we react.

00:32:44.100 --> 00:32:45.830 align:middle line:84%
We react automatically
to things.

00:32:45.830 --> 00:32:48.570 align:middle line:84%
So if even though if we may
say a positive affirmation,

00:32:48.570 --> 00:32:51.370 align:middle line:90%
we might not be aligned with it.

00:32:51.370 --> 00:32:53.580 align:middle line:90%
What's your advice?

00:32:53.580 --> 00:32:57.916 align:middle line:84%
I work on beliefs
quite a lot for myself.

00:32:57.916 --> 00:33:01.490 align:middle line:84%
We might think, I want
to get over there.

00:33:01.490 --> 00:33:03.060 align:middle line:84%
But a little belief,
a little voice,

00:33:03.060 --> 00:33:05.260 align:middle line:84%
that we perhaps
might have picked up

00:33:05.260 --> 00:33:07.700 align:middle line:84%
when we were younger,
children for example,

00:33:07.700 --> 00:33:09.530 align:middle line:84%
or even another
part of our lives,

00:33:09.530 --> 00:33:11.180 align:middle line:90%
that I'm not good enough.

00:33:11.180 --> 00:33:11.960 align:middle line:90%
I don't deserve that.

00:33:11.960 --> 00:33:14.680 align:middle line:84%
And I'm speaking from
personal experience here.

00:33:14.680 --> 00:33:17.700 align:middle line:84%
And I think many of the viewers
can probably relate to this.

00:33:17.700 --> 00:33:21.040 align:middle line:84%
But I grew up in a small
village in central Scotland

00:33:21.040 --> 00:33:25.560 align:middle line:84%
and the idea that we
are important isn't

00:33:25.560 --> 00:33:27.620 align:middle line:84%
something that you get
in that small village

00:33:27.620 --> 00:33:28.810 align:middle line:90%
in central Scotland.

00:33:28.810 --> 00:33:33.280 align:middle line:84%
In fact, you get the idea--
it's a small places and poverty

00:33:33.280 --> 00:33:35.240 align:middle line:84%
is a big thing in the
village I grew up in.

00:33:35.240 --> 00:33:40.060 align:middle line:84%
So people develop this idea that
not only are they not powerful,

00:33:40.060 --> 00:33:41.050 align:middle line:90%
but they're not import.

00:33:41.050 --> 00:33:43.170 align:middle line:84%
So I grew up in
that environment.

00:33:43.170 --> 00:33:45.920 align:middle line:84%
So when I started to
get on in my life,

00:33:45.920 --> 00:33:48.110 align:middle line:84%
it was so frustrating
because I had these beliefs,

00:33:48.110 --> 00:33:49.030 align:middle line:90%
I can do things.

00:33:49.030 --> 00:33:51.320 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that I
could explain stuff.

00:33:51.320 --> 00:33:53.080 align:middle line:84%
And I was a good
athlete and all that.

00:33:53.080 --> 00:33:55.560 align:middle line:84%
But this little voice kept
coming up and saying, ah,

00:33:55.560 --> 00:33:56.490 align:middle line:90%
but you're not good enough.

00:33:56.490 --> 00:33:57.550 align:middle line:90%
You don't deserve that.

00:33:57.550 --> 00:33:58.930 align:middle line:90%
You're rubbish.

00:33:58.930 --> 00:34:00.990 align:middle line:84%
Who are you to think
that you could speak

00:34:00.990 --> 00:34:03.560 align:middle line:84%
at the Hay House Conference?
this weekend?

00:34:03.560 --> 00:34:06.110 align:middle line:84%
Who are you to think you
deserve to be on that stage?

00:34:06.110 --> 00:34:09.650 align:middle line:84%
And that little voice, still
to this day, still to this day,

00:34:09.650 --> 00:34:10.650 align:middle line:90%
that little voice comes up.

00:34:10.650 --> 00:34:12.830 align:middle line:84%
And I think a lot
of public speakers,

00:34:12.830 --> 00:34:14.570 align:middle line:84%
even though we don't write
about it, we all share

00:34:14.570 --> 00:34:17.179 align:middle line:84%
the same-- we all have
our own little stuff.

00:34:17.179 --> 00:34:19.850 align:middle line:84%
And that little voice
comes up from time to time.

00:34:19.850 --> 00:34:20.550 align:middle line:90%
Who are you?

00:34:20.550 --> 00:34:22.440 align:middle line:90%
You don't deserve this.

00:34:22.440 --> 00:34:23.719 align:middle line:90%
And I have to work with that.

00:34:23.719 --> 00:34:25.055 align:middle line:84%
I've worked with it
a lot and the voice

00:34:25.055 --> 00:34:26.880 align:middle line:90%
has got quieter and quieter.

00:34:26.880 --> 00:34:28.040 align:middle line:90%
And it's belief work.

00:34:28.040 --> 00:34:32.790 align:middle line:84%
So I would write down on a
piece of paper how I'm feeling.

00:34:32.790 --> 00:34:34.350 align:middle line:90%
Why do I feel this way?

00:34:34.350 --> 00:34:37.179 align:middle line:84%
And I'd start to question
who I feel myself to be

00:34:37.179 --> 00:34:39.389 align:middle line:84%
and why do I believe
this about myself.

00:34:39.389 --> 00:34:42.290 align:middle line:84%
And eventually uncover
some ideas about myself.

00:34:42.290 --> 00:34:43.949 align:middle line:84%
And I replaced the
negative beliefs,

00:34:43.949 --> 00:34:46.560 align:middle line:84%
the disempowering little
voices, you're not good enough.

00:34:46.560 --> 00:34:49.219 align:middle line:84%
Who are you to be standing
on the stage for example.

00:34:49.219 --> 00:34:50.239 align:middle line:90%
You don't deserve this.

00:34:50.239 --> 00:34:52.424 align:middle line:84%
I replace it with
positive affirmations.

00:34:52.424 --> 00:34:54.600 align:middle line:90%
Or you're not to.

00:34:54.600 --> 00:34:55.940 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:34:55.940 --> 00:34:56.830 align:middle line:90%
I deserve these things.

00:34:56.830 --> 00:34:59.320 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
I've said a lot is I

00:34:59.320 --> 00:35:01.530 align:middle line:84%
live each day with
happiness and joy,

00:35:01.530 --> 00:35:04.050 align:middle line:84%
trusting only good
things come to me.

00:35:04.050 --> 00:35:08.630 align:middle line:84%
And I've used affirmations like,
I am a spark of the divine.

00:35:08.630 --> 00:35:10.840 align:middle line:84%
I am part of everything
that has ever been

00:35:10.840 --> 00:35:14.600 align:middle line:84%
and I absolutely deserve to
live a life of happiness and joy

00:35:14.600 --> 00:35:17.510 align:middle line:84%
and have anything that I
choose to create in my life.

00:35:17.510 --> 00:35:18.430 align:middle line:90%
Things like that.

00:35:18.430 --> 00:35:20.360 align:middle line:84%
And if you say them
over and over again,

00:35:20.360 --> 00:35:23.310 align:middle line:84%
the brain begins to process it
as if it's actually happening.

00:35:23.310 --> 00:35:26.230 align:middle line:84%
And we move towards what
we say about ourselves.

00:35:26.230 --> 00:35:29.390 align:middle line:84%
And the disempowering
beliefs work in the same way.

00:35:29.390 --> 00:35:32.850 align:middle line:84%
The little voice that comes
up all the time in our lives,

00:35:32.850 --> 00:35:34.400 align:middle line:84%
that we don't notice
it coming out,

00:35:34.400 --> 00:35:36.120 align:middle line:90%
but it's impacting the brain.

00:35:36.120 --> 00:35:37.200 align:middle line:90%
It's impacting the body.

00:35:37.200 --> 00:35:40.460 align:middle line:84%
And what it's doing is we're
moving towards that reality.

00:35:40.460 --> 00:35:42.880 align:middle line:84%
So when you identify
it, it empowers

00:35:42.880 --> 00:35:45.520 align:middle line:84%
you to realize that doesn't
need to have that power.

00:35:45.520 --> 00:35:47.310 align:middle line:84%
Then you replace it
with something positive.

00:35:47.310 --> 00:35:49.870 align:middle line:90%
So I've often had to do that.

00:35:49.870 --> 00:35:52.600 align:middle line:84%
And it's not like, I think
many people do belief work,

00:35:52.600 --> 00:35:54.790 align:middle line:90%
we think I've done it once.

00:35:54.790 --> 00:35:56.160 align:middle line:84%
And then things
worked for a while.

00:35:56.160 --> 00:35:58.620 align:middle line:84%
And then it seems an
issue comes back again.

00:35:58.620 --> 00:36:00.880 align:middle line:84%
People think, I must
have done it wrong.

00:36:00.880 --> 00:36:02.120 align:middle line:90%
I'm back in the same place.

00:36:02.120 --> 00:36:03.560 align:middle line:90%
But that's not the case.

00:36:03.560 --> 00:36:06.110 align:middle line:90%
Because life is cyclic.

00:36:06.110 --> 00:36:07.440 align:middle line:84%
There's a science
called chronobiology.

00:36:07.440 --> 00:36:09.690 align:middle line:84%
I have written about
it in my new book

00:36:09.690 --> 00:36:11.420 align:middle line:84%
and it's in the
film "Choice Point."

00:36:11.420 --> 00:36:12.920 align:middle line:90%
I am in that film.

00:36:12.920 --> 00:36:15.830 align:middle line:84%
And basically it shows
how cycles in the cosmos.

00:36:15.830 --> 00:36:18.400 align:middle line:90%
like the Earth spins.

00:36:18.400 --> 00:36:20.660 align:middle line:84%
As the Earth spins, the
sun goes across the sky.

